  "medicalDecision": "Acute unilateral colicky flank pain radiating to the groin with microscopic hematuria, afebrile, consistent with renal colic. No fever or signs of obstructing infection. Pain controlled with ketorolac and antiemetic; counseled on strain-urine, hydration, and urgent return for fever, intractable vomiting, or single kidney.",
  "prescriptions": [
    {
      "name": "ketorolac 10 mg tablet",
      "sig": "Take 1 tablet by mouth every 6 hours as needed for pain for up to 5 days"
    },
    {
      "name": "tamsulosin 0.4 mg capsule",
      "sig": "Take 1 capsule by mouth once daily to aid stone passage"
    },
    {
      "name": "ondansetron 4 mg ODT",
      "sig": "Dissolve 1 tablet on the tongue every 8 hours as needed for nausea"
    }
